## Summit Artifact 1: Spin a Dihedral Symmetry (Animate a Rosette)

**Goal:** Build a complete standalone program that generates a *D*₆ rosette (six-fold symmetry, like a snowflake) and displays the orbit of a seed curve.

```scheme
;; Summit: a D₆ rosette with a seed curve (a small arc).

(define G (alg/dihedral 6))

;; A seed point off the origin.
(define seed (geom/point 3 1))

;; Generate the orbit under the 6 rotations.
(define orbit (alg/rosette G seed))

;; For a richer visual, we'll also draw a small curve from the origin to the seed,
;; and rotate that curve six times.

(define seed-curve
  (let ((t-vals (map (lambda (i) (/ i 10.0)) (math/array 0 10))))
    (map (lambda (t)
           (geom/point (* 3 t) (* 1 t)))
         t-vals)))

;; Rotate the curve by multiples of 60° (2π/6).
(define rotated-curves
  (map (lambda (k)
         (let ((angle (/ (* 2 const/pi k) 6)))
           (map (lambda (p)
                  (let ((x (geom/point 'x p))
                        (y (geom/point 'y p)))
                    (geom/point
                      (- (* x (geom/cos angle)) (* y (geom/sin angle)))
                      (+ (* x (geom/sin angle)) (* y (geom/cos angle))))))
                seed-curve)))
       (math/array 0 5)))

;; Combine all six curves into a single plot.
(define plot-data
  (map (lambda (curve)
         (plot/line curve))
       rotated-curves))

(define scene (plot/with plot-data))

scene
;; => a plot object with six radial curves forming a rosette.
```

[VISUAL: A Cartesian plot showing six lines radiating from the origin, each a rotated copy of the seed curve, forming a six-fold symmetric rosette (like the spokes of a snowflake).]

<!-- BUILD: run top-to-bottom; the result is a plot structure with six line plots. Render as a Cartesian graph with all six curves overlaid, showing D₆ symmetry. This is the summit artifact for the dihedral branch. -->

**What it demonstrates:** The dihedral group *D*
")
